Rating: 4
This recipe is very good. (I added a teaspoon of garlic powder) Then I combined a cooking technique from a different recipe and had a huge winner! Instead of baking one loaf, I formed the meat mixture into smaller individual loaves. I browned them in a skillet with a little bit of olive oil, then topped them with a bit of HOMADE brand chili sauce and baked them on a broiling pan at 500 degrees (yes, 500) until the internal temp reached 160 degrees (10 - 15 minutes). A yummy keeper!

