Rating: 3
Easy and tasty. Both times I've made this to take for lunch at work, I've had co-workers commenting on how good it smells. The recipe also works fine with ground chicken. Note to those of you with gluten issues, or those of you who want an extra protein kick: in lieu of the breadcrumbs and milk, I cooked half a cup of quinoa, drained it and let it cool, then added it to the loaf mixture. The grain contributed nicely to the texture, and the nutty taste of quinoa worked well in the recipe.

